⏱️ Time Complexity:

👉 O(N × W)

Why?

States = (idx, W)
idx → N
W → 0 to W

So total states = N × W

Each state computed once due to memoization.

🧠 Space Complexity:

👉 O(N × W) + O(N)

Breakdown:

DP table: O(N × W)
Recursion stack: O(N)
🔥 Final Interview Answer:
Time: O(N × W)
Space: O(N × W) + O(N)

int knapsack(int W, vector<int> &val, vector<int> &wt) 
    {
        int n=val.size();
        vector<vector<int>> dp(n,vector<int>(W+1,0));
        //return helper(n-1,val,wt,W,dp);
        //base case
        for(int w = 0; w <= W; w++)
        {
            if(wt[0] <= w)
                dp[0][w] = val[0];
        }
        
        for(int idx=1;idx<n;idx++)
        {
            for(int w=0;w<=W;w++)
            {
                int take=0;
                if(wt[idx]<=w)
                {
                    take = val[idx]+dp[idx-1][w-wt[idx]];
                }
                int nottake = dp[idx-1][w];
                
                dp[idx][w] = max(take,nottake);
            }
        }
        return dp[n-1][W];
    }

⏱️ Time Complexity

👉 O(N × W)

Outer loop → N items
Inner loop → W capacity

So total = N × W

🧠 Space Complexity

👉 O(N × W)

DP table of size n × (W+1)
